%N A134090 Triangle, read by rows, where T(n,k) = [(I + D*C)^n](n,k); that is, row n of T = row n of (I + D*C)^n for n>=0 where C denotes Pascal's triangle, I the identity matrix and D a matrix where D(n+1,n)=1 and zeros elsewhere.
%C A134090 Column 0 equals A122455 if we define A122455(0)=1.
%F A134090 T(n,k) = [x^(n-k)] Sum_{j=0..n} C(n,j)*x^j/(1-j*x)^k /[Product_{i=0..j}(1-i*x)].
