%e A134090 Let P denote the matrix equal to Pascal's triangle shift down 1 row:
%e A134090 P(n,k) = C(n+1,k) for n>k>=0, with P(n,n)=1 for n>=0.
%e A134090 Illustrate row n of T = row n of P^n as follows.
